
@startuml

' Define classes
class Contract {
  +id: int
  +date: date
  +salesperson: Salesperson
  +acquisitions: List<Acquisition>
  +relatedAirline: Airline
}

class Acquisition {
  +id: int
  +contract: Contract
  +airplaneModel: String
  +price: double
  +options: List<String>
  +deliveryDate: date
}

class Salesperson {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +contracts: List<Contract>
}

class Airline {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +parentAirline: Airline
  +childrenAirlines: List<Airline>
}

class Airplane {
  +id: int
  +model: String
  +description: String
}

' Relationships
Contract "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : consists of
Contract "1" -- "1" Salesperson : managed by
Salesperson "1" -- "0..*" Contract : manages
Airline "1" -- "0..*" Airline : parent-child (one-way)
Airline "1" -- "0..*" Acquisition : buyer of
Acquisition "1" -- "1" Airplane : specifies model

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Contract`**: Represents a sales contract between Boeing and an airline. It contains multiple acquisitions, a salesperson, and optionally a related airline.
- **`Acquisition`**: Represents a specific airplane purchase under a contract. It includes details like model, price, options, and delivery date.
- **`Salesperson`**: Manages one or more contracts. A salesperson may change over time but is always assigned to a contract.
- **`Airline`**: Represents an airline company. It has a parent-child relationship with other airlines to track ownership structures.
- **`Airplane`**: Represents the model of the aircraft being sold.

